"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:3.21.5\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">3.21.5</span> 标题：脚镣（shackle, fetter, manacle）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">经文出处</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">来：כֶּבֶל</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：kevel)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps105:18\">PSA 105:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps149:8\">PSA 149:8</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">来：נְחֹשֶׁת</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：nchosheth)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg16:21\">JDG 16:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam3:34\">2SA 3:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs25:7\">2KI 25:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr33:11\">2CH 33:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:6\">2CH 36:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer39:7\">JER 39:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer52:11\">JER 52:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:7\">LAM 3:7</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希：πέδη</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：pedē)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:4\">MRK 5:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:4\">MRK 5:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:29\">LUK 8:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir6:24\">SIR 6:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir6:29\">SIR 6:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir21:19\">SIR 21:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir33:29\">SIR 33:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc3:41\">1MA 3:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/3Macc4:9\">3MA 4:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/3Macc6:19\">3MA 6:19</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希：χειροπέδη</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：cheiropedē)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir21:19\">SIR 21:19</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述和用途</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/WEB-0439_shackle.jpg\" alt=\"脚踝上的镣铐，用来限制囚犯的活动\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">脚踝上的镣铐，用来限制囚犯的活动 (Daderot, Public domain or CC0, via Wikimedia Commons)</figcaption></figure>脚镣是一种金属锁链，上面有专门的环，用来套住脚踝。脚镣的作用是限制危险分子或囚犯的行动。本条目与上一个条目“锁链、链子”有很多重叠之处。另参上节的插图。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">翻译</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>在有些语言中，“脚镣”的对等词就是“脚上的锁链”。<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:4\">MRK 5:4</a> 和<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:29\">LUK 8:29</a> 都提到锁链和脚镣。脚镣用来绑住腿和脚，而锁链用来绑住手和手臂。如果目标语言中没有具体指“脚镣”的词语，可把字面意思为“被锁链和脚镣捆绑”的短语译为：“给他的手脚套上锁链”。</p>\n<p>旧约文本通常会指明制作脚镣和锁链所用的材料。希伯来文<em>nchosheth</em> 指的是黄铜或青铜，而在《诗篇》中出现两次的<em>kevel</em> 指的是铁做的器具。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
